StoryAsset.name: Short Post Match Cup Leg 1 of 1 Rounds

keyValuePair.Value: Can you go all the way now?
That win takes you into the next round of the %1s. Congratulations. I know your boys will be celebrating but are you already thinking about how far you can go?
I think anything's possible.
Some of our attacking play today was exceptional. If the lads can reproduce that kind of performance in every round, then I wouldn't bet against us going all the way, to be honest.
It's about our own performances.

I though we looked really solid. Very composed. The boys did very well again and deserved the win. If we can sustain that level of performance then I think we can go on and do something special in this competition.
Let's not get ahead of ourselves.

I know it's been said before but we really do need to take one game at a time at the moment. Let's enjoy what we achieved with this win but we can't spend too long dreaming about the future. We need to focus on the next game and being properly prepared.
Are you happy with how comprehensive your victory was?
You didn't just win the game. You did it in style. And that means your boys are through to the next round. What did you make of the performance overall?
We're going to take some stopping!
We're going to take some stopping!

We controlled the game and it was a very good team performance. I think there's a lot of self-belief in our dressing room at the moment. Everybody's sure of the job they have to do and we trust each other. We know we've got the goals in us to win games.

We were good. And we can get better.

I think this group of players is really starting to develop as a team. They supported each other very well today. But I think there's more to come from them. If we're going to win trophies, I have to keep pushing them on to improve.
I want this win to count for something.

You work hard in training leading up to a game. But you never know exactly what will happen. It's a real pleasure when every single part of your plan comes good. Some of our attacking play was as good as I've ever seen from us.
Let's do that in every game!

The players have been working really hard in training. We want to function as a team unit as well as putting in good individual performances. The lads were great today and I want to see that kind of display in every game from now on.

I'm really pleased for the boys. We've been working hard in training and everything they tried came off today. A real boost for them. But let's keep our feet on the ground. We have to build on this performance now.
Did you miss a chance to progress today?
So %1s's progress ends with this defeat against %3s. What did you make of your team's performance? Are you disappointed to go out?
We were probably beaten by the better side.

Look, the boys gave it everything. But the opposition are a very experienced side and that made the difference in today's game. I'm sorry we're out but we must use this as a chance to learn lessons and improve.
We couldn't have done much more.

I was very impressed with our work rate and application today. The level of commitment from the lads was outstanding. I hope this result won't knock their confidence. They didn't deserve to lose here and I'm sure we can get back to winning ways soon.
We didn't take our chances.

When a game is all or nothing, you have to make your chances count. Maybe the pressure got to our players a little bit. This was a big occasion for all of us. But we kept making poor decisions in the final third and that was the difference between the two sides, probably.
That was a big defeat. What went wrong for you?
That was more than just a defeat. You were torn apart by %1s, weren't you? Could you have done better?
My boys need to take the criticism.

When you win, you take the praise. And when you lose, especially if you're beaten badly, you have to be ready for the criticism. I hope the harsh words will motivate them to make sure they're better next time out.

Our boys aren't at this level yet.

This team is a work in progress. The lads worked hard but they struggled against good players, and we never really did enough to give us a chance in the game. We'll be honest with ourselves after this defeat and come together to try to improve.
We were too easy to play against.

We had a plan but, for whatever reason, the boys didn't stick to it. We were all over the place defensively and that meant we never attacked with any fluency either. Really disappointing. I couldn't wait for it to be over, to be honest. We've got so much work to do.
